20140114 22:20:15 nbsp I think that Brisa has been nice the past two years I have lived here. I originally chose Brisa because of its location: closeness to Safeway and frequently running buses to campus. Soon afterward however, I have seen other good traits of Brisa. For the house itself, I think it is reasonably priced for the space that is rented out. The parking is also great, each unit has like 3 parking spaces, and plenty of parking in the front. But what I think makes Brisa a great place to live is the management. The management has excellent staff who really care about their clients. Thomas is a great manager, he is very quick, efficient, approachable, and professional. In addition other members like Elena, Jenna, Jeff, etc have all been pleasant in encounters and are quick to resolve problems. Even on finals week they provide residents with snacks and scantrons  aside from their cookies, coffee, and popcorn everyday in the office. Although the maintenance crew is limited in number, they have been able to complete a service request the same day I give it to the office. Under the same management, there are also Sorrento apartments and Avalon houses which seem to be great units. Overall, I feel like this management has a lot to offer: great units, great location, and great staff. Users/ElizabethDietz
